quotas.name: J&K Private Seats - Govt Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : J&K Private Seats - Govt Quota**

Domicile of UT of J&K /Ladakh. One of the below

1. 15 years resided in UT of JK and their children - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
2. Studied for 7 years and appeared for Class X/XII in JK and their children  - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
3. Registered as a migrant by the Relief and Rehabilitation Commissioner (Migrants) in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir (or)
4. Child of Central Govt employees, AIS, PSUs, Autonomous body of central Govts, PS Banks, Statutory Body officials, Central Univ and Recognized reserach institution of Central Govt officials having served in UT of JK for 10 years
5. Spouse of any such domicile

Domicile of UT of J&K /Ladakh. One of the below

1. 15 years resided in UT of JK and their children - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
2. Studied for 7 years and appeared for Class X/XII in JK and their children - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
3. Registered as a migrant by the Relief and Rehabilitation Commissioner (Migrants) in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir (or)
4. Child of Central Govt employees, AIS, PSUs, Autonomous body of central Govts, PS Banks, Statutory Body officials, Central Univ and Recognized reserach institution of Central Govt officials having served in UT of JK for 10 years
5. Spouse of any such domicile

**Eligibility for the Quota : J&K Govt Seats**

Domicile of UT of J&K /Ladakh. One of the below

1. 15 years resided in UT of JK and their children - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
2. Studied for 7 years and appeared for Class X/XII in JK and their children - even if the child residing outside due to business, vocation etc.. (or)
3. Registered as a migrant by the Relief and Rehabilitation Commissioner (Migrants) in the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir (or)
4. Child of Central Govt employees, AIS, PSUs, Autonomous body of central Govts, PS Banks, Statutory Body officials, Central Univ and Recognized reserach institution of Central Govt officials having served in UT of JK for 10 years
5. Spouse of any such domicile
